<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-27T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="967" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d967">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/63: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-27T23:00:00-04:00">October
                                    27, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1616. Although unable to delay all action by the Munitions Assignments
                            Board in London, the War Department states that the Board there has
                            agreed that the British are to furnish 2500 rifles and 125 Bren guns to
                            Saudi Arabia. There remain therefore a number of items that may be
                            furnished by this Government.</p>
                        <p>The foregoing is transmitted with reference to Department’s 1581, October
                            23, 1 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d967fn1">See footnote 99, above.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Please repeat to Jidda with reference to Department’s 92, October 23, 1
                            p.m. to Jidda.<note n="1" xml:id="d967fn2">See footnote 99,
                                above.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>